	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 30th 10:44 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>While AC comes in handy, as does stamina, and other melee stats, your druids overall usefullness will be bases on your wisdom.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sure, at low levels where you can step into combat and make a difference with your weapon its nice to have strong stats in those categories (and a decent weapon) at lvl 20 you are nearing a point where you will need to give up on these aspects of your life as a druid and become the caster that you will remain untill you get bored of kiting and pick a different class =)  Seriously, I have read plenty of posts saying druids can get in there and scrap too, and while they MIGHT be able to with a good weapon and the best gear suited for that style, there's simply no purpose to it.  You will get farther relying on your mana than on brawn.  SO, to answer your 'what armor?' question, theres lots of decent wis gear a druid can get for the couple of K you have to spend.  Braided ivy cords, splitpaw hide gloves, ulthork hide sleeves (i think those are the sleeves Im thinking of), mamoth hide cloak, othmir fur cap, a couple of RMBs (or chipped bone bracers to save a few plat)  wis jewelry for ears, fingers and face.  Plus, the brown chitin protector packs the most stats for a cheap price of any piece I've ever owned, and should keep your not as usefull stats at a respectable level.  I'm sure plenty of arguments can be made that this or that is better, but these items are cheap and easily attained, and make a good base at low lvls for a druid with a decent mana pool.  You can worry about Eboots, and direct-mana gear a little later in your career, but for now just try to focus on your caster aspect, as you will find your effectiveness with that weak druid weapon (Velium etched stone mace, centi warhammer, blackened mace will all serve as some main hand stats and a nice poker to save mana when the mobs low) dwindeling as your levels increase.  Feel free to disagree anybody, I am just offering my opinions as answer to this fledgeling druids queary =)  I hope this is of some help.<br><br>Ellayne Sedai- 43 Druid<br>Myrdraall Soulreamer-42 Shadowknight<br><br>Oh, and I just remembered...get your testament of vaneer as soon as possible.  Its a VERY easy quest, as the toughest part is waiting for 1 mob in Highhold to spawn, and gives great wis in offhand for minimal effort.  Untill then, go with charred guardian shield (i've seen them going for 75-100pp in the deflated economy of the new bazaar)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Jul 30 22:37:16 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
